26/10/2006
BUCHAREST, Romania -- Prime Minister Calin Popescu Tariceanu officially tapped a senator Wednesday (October 25) from his National Liberal Party, Varujan Vosganian, as the Romanian nominee for EU Commissioner.
Vosganian said it would be an honour to represent Romania in the Commission and indicated he would prefer a portfolio related to finance or culture.
The 48-year old Liberal, of ethnic Armenian origin, holds a Ph.D.
in Economics and is the author of numerous political and economic studies.
In other news, following the formal resignation Wednesday of suspended Defence Minister Teodor Atanasiu, Tariceanu nominated and President Traian Basescu formally decreed the appointment of Sorin Frunzaverde of the ruling Democratic Party.
He served as defence minister in 1999.
(Cotidianul, Ziua - 26/10/06;
Rompres, Mediafax - 25/10/06)
